      "text": "Conflict between Farmers and Fulani Herdsmen remains a persistent problem in Saki-West Local Government Area. In 1999, the conflict degenerated into violent clashes which resulted into monumental loss of lives on both sides. Many cows belonging to the Fulani were lost as collateral damage. Although, studies have been conducted on this subject, (e.g. Adebayo and Olaniyi, 2008; Albert, 2010) this research is aimed at examining the problems from different perspectives. "
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "0a97be317f4d5bd7",
      "text": "What are the traditional mechanisms of conflict resolution between Fulani cattle rearers and farmers and how successful have they been? Has government, at different levels, discharged its duties for peace and security in this area creditably and sincerely or are they part of the problem? Have security agencies been impartial in mediating between the conflicting parties? In considering the long term measure to resolving the problems, one solution that has been proffered is creation of grazing zones in the conflict - prone areas. How feasible is this solution? If creation of grazing zones cannot provide a long-term solution, then, alternative solution(s) should be proffered."
